The Lagos State House of Assembly has commended Lagos State University (LASU) for its attainment as the second best university in Nigeria,  the 11th in Africa and one of the first 500 in the world based on the latest world rating of universities.
The deputy clerk of the House, Taiwo Otun had during plenary yesterday read a letter signed by the Vice Chancellor of the University,  Professor Olanrewaju Fagbohun, and addressed to the Speaker, where he officially informed the Assembly of the ratings and thanked them for their support.
In his remarks the Speaker of the House, Rt. Hon. Mudashiru Obasa said that the management and students of LASU deserve commendation for the  height.
According to him, “I was amazed by the level of development on my recent visit to LASU, urging other lawmakers to pay a visit to the university to see things for themselves.
“LASU had always been at the forefront in the past and regaining it is pride of place in the academic circle worthy of celebration. We must celebrate them and congratulate the man at the helms of affairs in the university, Professor Olanrewaju Fagbohun,” Obasa declared.
The Speaker added that LASU was notable for crisis by the students of  the school, saying that this is no longer happening in the institution.
While commending both the executive and the legislative arms of the state for working together on the institution, the Speaker directed  that a letter of commendation should be written to the man-agement of  the institution.